    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Sedum caffrum are tincture, salve, tea, infusion, and infused oil. A tincture is prepared by soaking the plant's leaves and stems in a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin to extract its bioactive compounds. The salve is made by infusing the plant's leaves and stems in a carrier oil like coconut or olive oil to create a topical ointment for skin issues. Tea and infusion preparations involve steeping the plant's leaves and stems in hot water to release its flavonoids and other water-soluble compounds for oral consumption. Infused oil is prepared by infusing the plant's leaves and stems in a carrier oil to create a topical remedy for skin and wound healing.",
